Author: BARTON
Vol / Page: 33
Edition:
Quote: The most common condition affecting the penis and prepuce of rams is balano-posthitis or pizzle rot .. it may be necessary to carefully restrict the diet of male animals to produce an acid urine which will automatically clear minor external lesions of pizzle rot.
